            "url": "https://www.benzinga.com/25/04/44830360/bitcoin-ethereum-dogecoin-match-stock-futures-decline-as-nvidia-faces-pressure-analyst-sees-signs-of-resumption-o",
            "summary": "Cryptocurrencies and stock futures saw a dip as Nvidia Corp. (NASDAQ: NVDA) shares fell after the U.S. government mandated a license to export chips to China. Bitcoin dropped by 1.65% to $83,364.77, while Ethereum fell by 2.77% to $1,585.59, and Dogecoin decreased by 3.59% to $0.1534. In the past 24 hours, 97,198 traders were liquidated, with a total loss of $208.63 million, and $136 million in bullish bets were wiped out. Bitcoin's Open Interest reduced by 6.54%, but traders bought the dip, with the Long/Short Ratio rising above 1. Top gainers in 24 hours included MANTRA (OM) at 27.19%, DeXe (DEXE) at 6.26%, and Story (IP) at 5.64%. The global cryptocurrency market cap stood at $2.63 trillion.",
            "source_type": "news",
            "headline": "Bitcoin, Ethereum, Dogecoin drop in line with stock futures amid Nvidia's China chip export license news. BTC at $83,364.77 (-1.65%), ETH at $1,585.59 (-2.77%), DOGE at $0.1534 (-3.59%). 97,198 traders liquidated in the past 24 hours, with total liquidations at $208.63 million; $136 million in bullish bets erased due to pullback. MANTRA (OM) surges by 27.19%, DeXe (DEXE) by 6.26%, and Story (IP) by 5.64%. Global cryptocurrency market cap at $2.63 trillion.",
